text: The Monmouth County Park System is a department of Monmouth County, New Jersey that owns public parks and provides recreational activities. The Park System was created in 1960. Since that time, it has obtained over 18,000 acres of property and created dozes of parks throughout Monmouth County. The Park System was the first agency in the United States to be accredited by the Commission for Accreditation of Park and Recreation Agencies (CAPRA). It is still accredited today. == References == Category:Monmouth County, New Jersey Category:Parks in the United States
